Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu of Kebbi State has approved the release of a total of One hundred and fifty four million naira to Kaduna Electricity Distribution Company (KEDCO) to boost its revenue base of acquiring power from the Transmission Company of Nigeria (TCN). A statement signed by the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Abubakar Muazu Dakingari and made available to LEADERSHIP on Tuesday says the Commissioner for Water and Rural Development, Alhaji Nura Usman Kangiwa made this known in Birnin Kebbi on effort by the State Government to restoring regular electricity supply to the people in the state. Alhaji Nura Kangiwa made it clear that the incumbent administration of Senator Abubakar Atiku Bagudu has acknowledged the importance of electricity supply as the pillar of economic development of the society and would continue to accord utmost priority to the sector. The Commissioner affirmed that the state government would sustain its benevolence of providing financial back up to aid the revenue collection capacity of KEDCO to discharge its duty of power distribution efficiently and effectively. Consequently, he again advised consumers of Electricity to maintain regular payment of their bills to ensuring the provision of electricity supply on 24 hour basis. The Commissioner added that recently forty transformers have been installed in all parts of the state and about eighty new ones were purchased for the same purpose in furtherance of efforts to maintaining regular electricity supply to all communities.